forms of communication between mother and daughter, as well as to the female body. Sambuco also explores the attempts of the daughter-narrators to define a female self that is outside the constrictions of patriarchal society. Through these investigations, Corporeal Bonds identifies a strong connection between the ideas of post-Lacanian critical theorists, Italian feminist thinkers, and the stories within the novels.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aItalian fictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aItalian fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aMothers and daughters in literature. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Women Authors.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269949640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442699496423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442699496.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK